<!doctype html>
<html>
  <head>
    <style>
      @page {
        size: Letter;
        margin: 2.4cm 2cm;
        @top-center {
          content: string(chapter);
          font:
            8pt Georgia,
            serif;
          color: #667;
        }
        @bottom-center {
          content: counter(page);
          font:
            8pt Georgia,
            serif;
          color: #889;
        }
      }
      @page cover {
        margin: 0;
        @top-center {
          content: none;
        }
        @bottom-center {
          content: none;
        }
      }
      body {
        font-family: Georgia, "Times New Roman", serif;
        color: #1a1f2b;
        font-size: 11pt;
        line-height: 1.5;
        counter-reset: chap;
      }
      /* Sized to the exact Letter page (8.5in x 11in) so the gradient fills the whole cover page — 100vh is
     unreliable in the engine; break-after sends the table of contents to its own page. */
      .cover {
        page: cover;
        break-after: page;
        width: 8.5in;
        height: 11in;
        box-sizing: border-box;
        padding: 3cm;
        color: #fff;
        background: linear-gradient(155deg, #16233f 0%, #2c3f66 100%);
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        justify-content: center;
      }
      .cover img {
        height: 56px;
        width: auto;
        margin-bottom: 26pt;
      }
      .cover h1 {
        font-size: 30pt;
        margin: 0 0 10pt;
        letter-spacing: 0.4px;
      }
      .cover .sub {
        font-size: 13pt;
        color: #cfd9ee;
        line-height: 1.6;
      }
      nav.toc {
        break-after: page;
      }
      nav.toc h2 {
        font-size: 16pt;
        color: #16233f;
        border-bottom: 2px solid #16233f;
        padding-bottom: 6pt;
        margin: 0 0 12pt;
      }
      nav.toc ol {
        list-style: none;
        padding: 0;
        margin: 0;
      }
      nav.toc li {
        margin: 0 0 9pt;
      }
      nav.toc a {
        text-decoration: none;
        color: #1a1f2b;
      }
      nav.toc a::after {
        content: leader(". ") target-counter(attr(href), page);
        color: #667;
      }
      h1.chapter {
        break-before: page;
        font-size: 18pt;
        color: #16233f;
        margin: 0 0 8pt;
        padding-bottom: 4pt;
        border-bottom: 1px solid #d7dbe4;
        counter-increment: chap;
        bookmark-level: 1;
        bookmark-label: content();
        string-set: chapter counter(chap) ". " content();
      }
      h1.chapter::before {
        content: counter(chap) ". ";
        color: #6b7a99;
      }
      h2 {
        font-size: 12.5pt;
        color: #2c3f66;
        margin: 14pt 0 5pt;
        bookmark-level: 2;
      }
      p {
        margin: 0 0 9pt;
        text-align: justify;
      }
      .note {
        background: #f3f5f9;
        border-left: 3px solid #16233f;
        padding: 8pt 12pt;
        margin: 12pt 0;
        font-size: 10pt;
        break-inside: avoid;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <section class="cover">
      <img
        src="{{{assets.northwind-logo.v1}}}"
        alt="{{parameterSets.disclosures.v1.bankname}} logo"
      />
      <h1>{{parameterSets.disclosures.v1.bankname}}</h1>
      <div class="sub">
        Deposit Compliance Handbook<br />{{data.edition}} · Effective
        {{data.effectiveDate}}
      </div>
    </section>
    <nav class="toc">
      <h2>Contents</h2>
      <ol>
        <li><a href="#ch-scope">Scope &amp; regulatory basis</a></li>
        <li><a href="#ch-disclosures">Required customer disclosures</a></li>
        <li><a href="#ch-review">Review &amp; sign-off obligations</a></li>
        <li><a href="#ch-records">Records &amp; retention</a></li>
      </ol>
    </nav>
    <h1 class="chapter" id="ch-scope">Scope &amp; regulatory basis</h1>
    <p>
      This handbook governs every customer-facing deposit document Northwind
      Financial publishes — rate sheets, account disclosures, and statements. It
      codifies the controls that keep those documents accurate, compliant, and
      traceable from draft to publication.
    </p>
    <h2>Applicability</h2>
    <p>
      The controls in this handbook apply to all deposit product lines and to
      every team that authors, reviews, or publishes a customer-facing document,
      regardless of channel.
    </p>
    <div class="note">{{parameterSets.disclosures.v1.fdicnotice}}</div>
    <h1 class="chapter" id="ch-disclosures">Required customer disclosures</h1>
    <p>
      Every published rate or account document must carry the applicable
      regulatory disclosures in full and unabridged form. Annual Percentage
      Yields are stated as of an effective date, and any condition that could
      reduce earnings — fees, minimum balances, early-withdrawal penalties — is
      disclosed alongside the yield.
    </p>
    <h2>Placement</h2>
    <p>
      Disclosures appear on the same document as the figures they qualify; a
      reference to a separate document does not satisfy this requirement.
    </p>
    <h1 class="chapter" id="ch-review">Review &amp; sign-off obligations</h1>
    <p>
      No deposit document is published until it clears the full approval
      pipeline: engineering, product, legal &amp; compliance, and marketing each
      sign off in order. A stage may not be skipped, and an unresolved review
      comment blocks final approval.
    </p>
    <h2>Segregation of duties</h2>
    <p>
      The author of a version may not approve their own stage. Each sign-off is
      attributed to a named approver and recorded in the immutable audit trail.
    </p>
    <h1 class="chapter" id="ch-records">Records &amp; retention</h1>
    <p>
      The full chain of custody for every published version — authorship, each
      stage sign-off, the resolved review thread, and the publication event — is
      retained for the regulatory retention period and is available for
      examination on request.
    </p>
    <div class="note">{{parameterSets.disclosures.v1.contact}}</div>
  </body>
</html>
